    <abstract>
      <t>The IS-IS routing protocol uses TLV (Type-Length-Value) encoding in a variety of protocol messages. The original IS-IS TLV definition allows for 255 octets of value in maximum. This document proposes a backward compatible IS-IS extension for encoding the TLV whose value is bigger than 255 octets.</t>
